captions.text: - Well hello everyone.
My name is Tyler Oakley,
and I feel like it has been forever
since I answered any of your questions.
So I thought, you know what,
let's just get down to business.

Not to defeat the Huns but
instead to answer your questions,
because it is time for another Q and Slay.
My good friend, Julie, would like to know

what fast food could
you never live without?
And, I mean, it's hard for me to decide.

It's like you know the
movie, Sophie's Choice,

where she has to choose which
of her children must die?

My version of Sophie's
Choice would have to be
Taco Bell and Panda Express.
I can't not love both of my children.
I can't kill one or the other.
I need them both in my life.
To survive, I need them both.
Good question, Julie.
Brownie_Hugger would like to know
what color is North West antichrist red?
So if you listen to the podcast,

you would know all about
North West antichrist red.
I'm not going to get into it.

Listen to the podcast
if you'd like to know
what we are talking about, but let me see.
The outfit that Grace Helbig is wearing

on the cover of her new
book, Grace's Guide,
which you can get in bookstores or online.
The link is below.

Bailey would like to know,
are you hella Christmas?
And I would have to say,

as soon as like the minute
is past, Halloween is over,
November 1st, it's Christmas music time.
Do not disturb.
In fact, I have been like listening
to Christmas music since July.
I am ready.

The new Pentatonix
Christmas album, incredible.
Love it.
Enjoy it.
Get it.
You're gonna die.
Lydia would like to know,

what are you recommending
this month on Audible?

And as you guys know, I
recommend a new book every month.

We have a little book
club going on right here.
If you use audible.com/tyleroakley,
you get your first book free,
but you can pick any book.
They have over 150,000 titles.
I recommend a book every single month.
This month I am recommending Gone Girl.
I was obsessed with the movie.
I saw it before I read the book.
Now I'm reading the book,
and it's like so true to like the movie.
So, I'm like very happy about it.

And everyone that's read
the book that saw the movie
said that they like match up perfectly.
So, I'm like loving it.
It is a roller coaster.
Get it.
If you want to listen to it,
get it at audible.com/tyleroakley.

Again, if you use that link,
you get your first burk free.
First brick free.
First book free.
You get your first book free.
You're welcome in advance.
BoomitsHannah says, I wanna know
how cute are you feeling today?
I'm feeling pretty cute.
Honestly, I feel pretty cute today.
I got this shirt I think in my P.O. Box,
and I really like it.
It shows off my beautiful muscles,
because I'm such a jock.
(laughs)
But yes, I am feeling cute today.
I was like, can I wear a sleeveless shirt?
I don't really know

But then I saw, this morning,
Troye Sivan's new video,

and it's all about life is
not about finding yourself.

It's about creating
yourself and doing things

that you want to do because
you want to do them,
and life is all about taking those risks.

To take that risk that
nobody else will make
is what's going to set you apart.
And so I was like, you know what?
Sleeveless shirt today.
Thanks Troye.

Haley says, how do you
feel about this picture?
(laughs)

When I saw it, I was like
okay, well, thank you for that.

Honestly, it kind of freaks me
out in the best way possible.

If there's somebody out
there with a foot fetish,

they are living their life by
watching this video right now.
So thank you for giving that to them.
But honestly, every time I make a video

I like log into Tumblr
like a minute after,
and there's already things like this,

and I'm like, if there's one
thing that I am impressed by
it's my people, because they are quick
and they are talented.
Rachrach would like to know,
are you sad to be leaving Top That?
As you guys know, I was a part of

a weekly pop culture countdown
show called Top That.

If you want to check it
out, the link is below.
It's still going to go on,
but I am actually moving on from the show.
I am focusing on some other projects
that I have wanted to work on for a while,

but I don't like to divvy up
my time and slice up who I am

and kind of give half-assed
efforts into different projects.
If I'm working on something,

I want to give 100% of
myself to something.
So with that in mind, I was like

Becca, I want you to go full
speed ahead with Top That.
I am going to go down this path

and work on these things that
I've always dreamed to do.

Em would like to know, left
butt cheek or right butt cheek?

And honestly, my left
butt cheek is ecstasy.
My right butt cheek is bliss.
Try pickin between em.
Girl, it's impossible.
Honestly, I'm not gonna lie.
I've got a nice ass butt.
Nice ass-butt.
Nice (laughs) ass-butt.
Yep, I've got a nice ass-butt.
I am a cutie patootie with a rad ass booty

that all the boys are
going to line up for,

whether it's your brother or
your dad or your boyfriend.
So, sorry about it.
Zoe says, what is your favorite
Psycho Babble episode so far?
(grunts)
Oh my gosh.
I can't.
Honestly, I can't pick.
They literally get better every week.
The latest one was so funny.
It was like a Halloween episode.
But the future one is even better.
It's like all about boys.
So, it's just listen.
Go subscribe on iTunes.

Homiephan wants to know, what
is the best website ever?

I would probably have to go
with tyleroakleytour.com.

But yes, that is all I
have for you guys today.

If you also are a cutie
patootie with a rad ass booty,
give this video a thumbs up.
I will love you forever if you do.

I think we can get 100,000
thumbs up in the first day.
I think we can do it.
Go push the thumbs up button.
I'm waiting.
There we go.
Thank you.

If you'd like to see my latest
video, click right there.
It's my Halloween costume from this year,
and it was adorable.

If you'd like to hear my latest
podcast, click right there.
It's all about Taylor Swift.
We are celebrating 1989.

It is kind of the best
episode yet, dare I say it.
Go listen and subscribe on iTunes.

And if you'd like to be
my person of the week,
click right there.

But yes, that is all I have
for you guys this week.
I hope you have a fabulous life,
and I will see you guys next time.
Later.
